+frameInbox('Patterns in other games')
	div
		ul
			li.italic.fragment Interesting but incomplete information can motivate exploration<br> in a variety of ways
			li.fragment <span class="highlight">Design Problem:</span> Designers need to motivate their players<br> to explore the worlds they create.
			li.fragment <span class="highlight">Pattern Description:</span> A designer may present the player with<br> compelling but incomplete pieces of information, and then give the player gameplay avenues that will allow them to seek out more information and solve the mysteries.
			li.fragment <span class="highlight">Example Games:</span>
				ul
					li.fragment Grand Theft Auto IV - a map shows the quests you can do in the area surrounding you at the moment
					li.fragment Skyrim - a horizontal compass in your HUD shows nearby quests and point of interest.
					li.fragment Dear Esther - a narrative voiceover that's compelling but vague
